{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban naming of suspects unless guilt is proven",
        "additional_details": "We think this will protect fairness and justice for all.\r\n\r\nI want the government to ban publishing suspect names during proceedings to protect those who may be innocent. If a suspect is named and later found not guilty, their reputation and future can be ruined by a trial in the court of public opinion.",
        "background": "Article 6 of the European Convention on Human Rights ensures the right to a fair trial. To uphold the \"innocent until proven guilty\" principle, a new law should ban the naming of suspects before conviction, regardless of case severity or media pressure. ",
